# Info

Invoked when a level/dimension is unloaded.

# Available Event Fields

- `event.level` - The level that was unloaded

# Example

```js
LevelEvents.unloaded(event => {
	console.log(`Level unloaded: ${event.level.dimension}`)
})

// Listen for specific dimension
LevelEvents.unloaded('minecraft:the_end', event => {
	console.log('The End has been unloaded!')
})
```
